WEBVTT

00:06.473 --> 00:12.277
♪♪

00:12.279 --> 00:17.349
Joe: When I think of legacy,
I think of this.

00:17.351 --> 00:21.420
An old man giving a young boy
a horseshoe.

00:21.422 --> 00:22.887
I don't know why,

00:22.889 --> 00:25.023
But it perfectly captures
what it feels like

00:25.025 --> 00:27.692
To be given something
by an old person.

00:27.694 --> 00:29.027
You don't want it,

00:29.029 --> 00:31.496
But you're getting it
and have to keep it.

00:31.498 --> 00:34.433
It reminds me of nfl teams.

00:35.836 --> 00:39.438
It's almost like you're handed
down an nfl team at birth.

00:39.440 --> 00:42.574
Some people are fortunate
to be given a dynasty

00:42.576 --> 00:44.777
That keeps winning
no matter what.

00:44.779 --> 00:46.911
Oh, well.
What?

00:46.913 --> 00:50.449
Oh, well.
Yeah. Oh, well.

00:50.451 --> 00:53.117
Others have to deal with
decades of disappointment.

00:53.119 --> 00:58.122
I was one of the lucky ones,
as my nana was a packers fan.

00:58.124 --> 01:00.124
Did you know that
the green bay packers

01:00.126 --> 01:02.461
Are owned by its fans.

01:02.463 --> 01:05.330
It's true.
The town currently has

01:05.332 --> 01:09.934
360,760 stockholders

01:09.936 --> 01:17.676
Who collectively own 5,011,558
shares of the franchise.

01:17.678 --> 01:20.545
People pass their shares
down to their children,

01:20.547 --> 01:24.949
Creating generations
of invested fans.

01:24.951 --> 01:26.885
Now, that's a legacy.

01:30.957 --> 01:34.226
Hello. My name's joe pera.

01:34.228 --> 01:38.497
And I'm at the melskys' to watch
the nfc championship game.

01:38.499 --> 01:41.099
Unfortunately,
without the packers.

01:41.101 --> 01:44.369
With a final record of 6-9-1,

01:44.371 --> 01:46.771
This past year's season
is something

01:46.773 --> 01:49.641
I don't want to talk about.

01:49.643 --> 01:52.244
We lost to the bears.

01:52.246 --> 01:55.647
Still, the game
is a good distraction.

01:55.649 --> 01:58.517
I finally put my nana's house
on the market.

01:58.519 --> 02:00.252
And this afternoon
is the first open --

02:00.254 --> 02:02.254
[ cheering ]
open house.

02:02.256 --> 02:07.125
[ cheering continues ]

02:07.127 --> 02:09.061
Did I miss a touchdown?

02:09.063 --> 02:11.396
No,
it's a godaddy commercial.

02:11.398 --> 02:12.797
Godaddy!

02:12.799 --> 02:17.936
[ cheering ]

02:17.938 --> 02:24.677
♪♪

02:24.679 --> 02:31.149
♪♪

02:31.151 --> 02:33.151
Brad: We have some wow.

02:33.153 --> 02:37.222
And then we have
some more wow.

02:37.224 --> 02:38.623
Joe, we did it.

02:38.625 --> 02:41.560
I mean, this place really has
an authentic brooklyn feel.

02:41.562 --> 02:43.562
Sure.

02:43.564 --> 02:46.498
But what about all
the sentimental value?

02:46.500 --> 02:49.167
Joe, if sentimental value
was factored in,

02:49.169 --> 02:51.369
I could sell this place
for $35 million,

02:51.371 --> 02:53.705
But unfortunately
it's not.

02:53.707 --> 02:55.974
