02:55.976 --> 02:57.442
Right.

02:57.444 --> 02:59.043
Do you want me
to stick around

02:59.045 --> 03:00.579
To tell people about
all the memories?

03:00.581 --> 03:02.647
Oh, look, joe, joe,
I know these buyers.

03:02.649 --> 03:04.583
When they walk
through this door,

03:04.585 --> 03:06.585
They just want a tall drink of
water real-estate agent

03:06.587 --> 03:09.187
Like myself
to smooth-talk them.

03:09.189 --> 03:11.590
But if you're here
telling them about nana,

03:11.592 --> 03:13.926
People are gonna start saying,
"cool story, bro,"

03:13.928 --> 03:15.728
Trust me.

03:15.730 --> 03:17.662
Right.

03:17.664 --> 03:20.733
Hey, why don't you and sarah
go see a motion picture?

03:20.735 --> 03:24.136
The melskys actually invited us
over to watch the big game.

03:24.138 --> 03:25.470
Oh, that's great.

03:25.472 --> 03:29.074
Beer, sports, and wings,
aka my religion.

03:29.076 --> 03:30.675
[ chuckles ]

03:30.677 --> 03:33.746
Sarah's there now
with her new friend debin.

03:33.748 --> 03:35.413
Debin jaconski-hammershunk?

03:35.415 --> 03:37.616
Yeah. You know her?

03:37.618 --> 03:39.684
Yeah, yeah.

03:39.686 --> 03:40.552
[ sighs ]

03:40.554 --> 03:44.022
Well, she was
the one that got away.

03:44.024 --> 03:45.991
Sorry.
I don't care.

